"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:3.21.4\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">3.21.4</span> 标题：锁链、链子（chain）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">经文出处</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：אֲזִקִּים</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：’aziqim（’azeq的复数）)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer40:1\">JER 40:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer40:4\">JER 40:4</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：זֵק</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：ziqim（zeq的复数）)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job36:8\">JOB 36:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps149:8\">PSA 149:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:14\">ISA 45:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:10\">NAM 3:10</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：מַעֲדַנּוֹת</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：ma‘adanoth)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:31\">JOB 38:31</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：מֹשְׁכוֹת</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：moshkoth)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:31\">JOB 38:31</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：רַתּוּקָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：ratuqah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:21\">1KI 6:21</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：ἅλυσις</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：halusis)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:3\">MRK 5:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:4\">MRK 5:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:4\">MRK 5:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:29\">LUK 8:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:6\">ACT 12:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:7\">ACT 12:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:33\">ACT 21:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:20\">ACT 28:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:20\">EPH 6:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:16\">2TI 1:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:1\">REV 20:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis17:16\">WIS 17:16</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：δέσμιος, δεσμός</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：desmios, desmos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:29\">LUK 8:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:16\">LUK 13:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:26\">ACT 16:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:23\">ACT 20:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:29\">ACT 23:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:29\">ACT 26:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:31\">ACT 26:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:7\">PHP 1:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:14\">PHP 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:17\">PHP 1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:18\">COL 4:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:9\">2TI 2:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:10\">PHM 1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:13\">PHM 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:36\">HEB 11:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:6\">JUD 1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis10:14\">WIS 10:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir6:25\">SIR 6:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir6:30\">SIR 6:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir13:12\">SIR 13:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir28:20\">SIR 28:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir28:20\">SIR 28:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir28:20\">SIR 28:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/3Macc3:25\">3MA 3:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/3Macc4:7\">3MA 4:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/3Macc5:6\">3MA 5:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/3Macc6:27\">3MA 6:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/4Macc12:2\">4MA 12:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Esd1:38\">1ES 1:38</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：σειρά</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：seira)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:4\">2PE 2:4</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/OAI-0035_fetters_chains_hans.jpg\" alt=\"锁链和脚镣\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">锁链和脚镣 (Image generated by ChatGPT using OpenAI technology)</figcaption></figure>锁链是一串链环连在一起，通常由金属做成。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>锁链通常用于限制物体，或把几个物体固定在一起。它尤其与限制囚犯的行动有关。另参<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">10.5.4 项链、链、带子 (necklace, chain, cord)&lt;REALIA:10.5.4&gt;</a> 。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻译</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>在许多语言中，“锁链”的表达方式就是“金属绳”。还有一些语言可以译为“一节节的绳子”，而不是“扭绞的绳子”，后者是指用某种纤维编成的绳子。有些语言用不同的词语表示捆绑人的锁链与工农业生产所用的链条。</p>\n<p>在上面列出的一些经文中，“锁链”象征监禁。在类似<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:7\">PHP 1:7</a> 的经文中，许多译本都会遵循<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 的译法。在这节经文的中间部分，希腊文本的字面意思是“在我被锁链捆绑的境地中”，但<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 英文意为“现在我在狱中的情况下”。</p>\n<p>所罗门放在至圣所前的链子是用金子做的（<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:21\">1KI 6:21</a> ），主要用来装饰，但它们也提醒在圣所供职的人不要靠近至圣所。</p>\n<p>在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:31\">JOB 38:31</a> 中，有两个希伯来文词语需要特别注意。<em>ma‘adanoth</em> （也出现在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:32\">1SA 15:32</a> ，意思却完全不同）与一个意为“系、绑”的动词一起出现。<em>ma‘adanoth</em> 的意思不确定，但似乎是由于“环”一词中的两个希伯来文字母调换了顺序所导致的，所以<em>ma‘adanoth</em> 的意思是一串相互连接的环，即“链子”（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 直译）。有些译本倾向于将动词和名词合译为“系在一起”（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"German Common Language Version (Gute Nachricht Bibel)\">GECL</abbr> 直译），而不提捆绑所用的物件。第二个希伯来文词语<em>moshkoth</em> 在整本圣经中仅出现在此处。该词来自一个意为“拉、拖”的动词。在现代希伯来文中，<em>moshkoth</em> 的意思是“缰绳”（用来驾驭马的皮绳），<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Jewish Publication Society Version\">NJPSV</abbr> 的译法就反映出这一层意思，这节经文的第二行英文意为“或解开猎户座的缰绳”。其他译本认为<em>moshkoth</em> 指的是猎户座的“腰带”（如<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New English Bible (1970)\">NEB</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised English Bible (1989)\">REB</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"German Common Language Version (Gute Nachricht Bibel)\">GECL</abbr> ），这是排成一行的三颗星。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps149:8\">PSA 149:8</a> ：<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 在这节经文的英文意为，“用链子捆绑他们的君王，用铁脚镣锁住他们的贵族。”“他们的贵族”与“他们的君王”平行，指军事领袖。在一些语言中，使用“链子”和“铁脚镣”容易让人以为捆绑君王的链子不是用铁做成的。然而，诗歌中的平行表明它们是同义词。在一些语言中，这节经文可译为：“俘虏他们的君王和领袖，并把他们绑起来。”</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:1\">REV 20:1</a> ：“一条大锁链”（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 直译）可以译为“一条沉重的锁链”（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 直译）或“一条粗锁链”。我们假定这条链子是金属做成的，目的显然是捆绑撒但。在金属锁链不为人所知的文化中，翻译者可以说“一根粗绳子”，或者也可以使用其他用来绑人的材料。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
